%20alt%3D%5C%22Krishna%20Ganeriwal%20headshot%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68221faf3fe8d392836592da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222304%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Meta%20senior%20software%20engineer%20shared%204%20strategies%20for%20career%20growth%20in%20times%20of%20uncertainty.%3Cp%3EKrishna%20Ganeriwal%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EKrishna%20Ganeriwal%2C%20a%20Meta%20software%20engineer%2C%20shared%20four%20strategies%20that%20helped%20grow%20his%20career.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMeta's%20'year%20of%20efficiency'%20led%20to%20structural%20changes%20and%2010%2C000%20employees%20being%20laid%20off%20in%202023.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAligning%20with%20company%20priorities%20and%20tackling%20overlooked%20tasks%20can%20help%20career%20advancement%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Krishna%20Ganeriwal%2C%20a%20senior%20engineer%20at%20Meta%20in%20California.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMeta%20dubbed%202023%20its%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-year-of-efficiency-working-meta-ai-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3Byear%20of%20efficiency%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20made%20several%20changes%20to%20the%20company's%20structure%2C%20including%20flattening%20management%20layers%20and%20laying%20off%20about%2010%2C000%20employees.%20This%20interview%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20Ganeriwal's%20employment%20history%20and%20compensation.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20moved%20to%20the%20US%20in%202021%20for%20my%20master's%2C%20after%20working%20for%20four%20years%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%20at%20Texas%20Instruments%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20before%20I%20graduated%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Wisconsin-Madison%2C%20I%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20intern%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20loved%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20projects%20the%20company%20worked%20on%2C%20and%20I%20returned%20to%20the%20company%20full%20time%20as%20a%20software%20engineer%20in%202023%20%E2%80%94%20Meta's%20%26quot%3Byear%20of%20efficiency.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20four%20strategies%20I%20used%20to%20get%20promoted%20and%20grow%20my%20salary%20from%20%24200%2C000%20to%20about%20%24500%2C000%20in%20the%2018%20months%20since%20I%20joined%20full%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225900736c-8e1f-4b8e-b5d4-1f8ba1c2c047%5C%22%3E1.%20Swim%20with%20the%20tide%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20company%20management%20is%20working%20toward%20a%20theme%2C%20which%20was%20efficiency%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Meta%2C%20I%20see%20it%20as%20a%20direct%20hint%20for%20what%20my%20priorities%20need%20to%20be.%20I%20tried%20to%20align%20myself%20with%20the%20same%20idea%20of%20efficiency%20over%20scaling%20and%20growth%20at%20all%20costs%2C%20which%20was%20the%20mindset%20many%20tech%20companies%20had%20previously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20meant%20taking%20note%20of%20my%20knowledge%20gaps%20and%20upskilling%20so%20that%20I%20can%20help%20build%20more%20cost-aware%20infrastructure.%20Reorganizations%20and%20layoffs%20are%20times%20of%20major%20cost%20cutting%2C%20and%20it%20would%20be%20swimming%20against%20the%20tide%20to%20insist%20on%20working%20on%20time-consuming%20or%20expensive%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20it%20helpful%20to%20have%20an%20open%20ear%20to%20what%20company%20leaders%20are%20talking%20about%20at%20quarterly%20meetings%20and%20constantly%20ensure%20that%20I%20am%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20%E2%80%94or%20at%20least%20the%20periphery%20of%20%E2%80%94%20those%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bfb97ae6-172b-48d1-86a8-0393527d65cb%5C%22%3E2.%20Get%20ready%20to%20reprioritize%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20because%20you've%20been%20fortunate%20to%20survive%20a%20round%20of%20layoffs%2C%20it%20doesn't%20mean%20there's%20nothing%20for%20you%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tell%20myself%20that%20a%20layoff%20means%20I%20have%20to%20be%20ready%20to%20be%20thrown%20into%20ambiguous%20areas%20and%20solve%20problems%2C%20despite%20constraints%20such%20as%20fewer%20colleagues%20and%20fewer%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20means%20I%20have%20to%20be%20open%20to%20pivoting%20and%20reprioritizing%20%E2%80%94%20dropping%20what%20I'm%20working%20on%20at%20the%20moment%20and%20switching%20priorities%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20temporarily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220171802b-2b79-4516-bd90-9f1cca3b35db%5C%22%3E3.%20Don't%20put%20your%20growth%20in%20the%20backseat%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20it%20helpful%20to%20separate%20conversations%20about%20layoffs%20and%20the%20company's%20performance%20from%20those%20about%20my%20career%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20multiple%20rounds%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-low-performance-cuts-review-cycle-politics-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elayoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20company%2C%20I%20kept%20having%20conversations%20with%20my%20manager%20about%20setting%20new%20goals%20for%20myself%20and%20working%20toward%20them.%20I%20also%20took%20steps%20to%20overcommunicate%20and%20remain%20visible%20to%20my%20manager%20and%20others%20in%20my%20team%20because%20it%20plays%20an%20important%20role%20during%20performance%20reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229b0271c4-6d36-4cdd-9ebd-6f8234d45673%5C%22%3E4.%20Be%20open%20to%20'underdog'%20problems%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20underrated%20strategy%20that%20helped%20me%20land%20promotions%20was%20looking%20out%20for%20problems%20and%20tasks%20no%20one%20was%20willing%20to%20work%20on%2C%20because%20they%20were%20likely%20busy%20chasing%20a%20piece%20of%20a%20big%2C%20exciting%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%2